<p>I am using <a href="https://developers.google.com/chart/interactive/docs/gallery/timeline#Configuration_Options" rel="nofollow">GoogleVis to plot timeline charts</a>. Here is a sample code example  from <a href="http://jason.bryer.org/" rel="nofollow">Jason Bryer's timeline package</a>, showing the US presidents and UK prime ministers during World War II. :</p>  <pre><code>require(timeline) require(googleVis)  data(ww2) ww2$Person &lt;- gsub("\\n" ," ", ww2$Person) plot(gvisTimeline(ww2, barlabel="Person", rowlabel="Group",                        start="StartDate", end="EndDate",      options=list(width=590), chartid="ww2") ) </code></pre>  <p><strong>My question:</strong> How to add a title to the Timeline chart? I tried the following but it did not work:</p>  <pre><code>plot(gvisTimeline(ww2, barlabel="Person", rowlabel="Group",                            start="StartDate", end="EndDate",          options=list(width=590), title="Timeline Chart", chartid="ww2")     ) </code></pre>